With respect to each User, this MISA, any exhibits, schedules and appendices hereto, together with such User’s Service Agreement, shall be referred to as the “Agreement” between such User and the other parties hereto. RECITALS A. Interconnection Provider owns certain interconnection and related facilities under development and intends to construct, own and operate an approximately 14.5 mile, single-circuit 220kV line with 1,150MWac capacity from a Project substation to SCE’s Windhub Substation (the “Gen-Tie Line”). The Gen-Tie Line will use a mix of overhead and underground spans and use of both public and private rights of way. B. BF1, a limited liability company organized and existing under the laws of the State of Delaware, owns a solar-plus-storage project under development, totaling 500 MWac of solar and related battery storage capacity (the “BF1 Project”). C. BF1 has entered into an interconnection agreement with Southern California Edison Company (“Transmission Owner” or “SCE”) and California Independent System Operator Corporation (“CAISO”) dated May 7, 2020, providing for up to a total capacity at the Point of Interconnection (as defined below) of 500 MWac (the “BF1 LGIA”). D. 26SB 8me LLC, a limited liability company organized and existing under the laws of the State of Delaware (“BF2”), owns a solar-plus-storage project under development, totaling 500 MWac of solar and related battery storage capacity (the “BF2 Project”). E. BF2 has entered into an interconnection agreement with the Transmission Owner and CAISO dated February 7, 2021, providing for up to a total capacity at the Point of Interconnection of 500 MWac (the “BF2 LGIA”). F. 51LV 8me LLC, a limited liability company organized and existing under the laws of the State of Delaware (“BF3”), owns a solar-plus-storage project under development, totaling 150 MWac of solar and related battery storage capacity (the “BF3 Project”). G. BF3 has entered into an interconnection agreement with the Transmission Owner and CAISO dated as of June 28, 2023, providing for up to a total capacity at the Point of Interconnection of 150 MWac (the “BF3 LGIA” and, together with the BF1 LGIA and the BF2 LGIA, and the interconnection agreements with the Transmission Owner and CAISO entered into by any other User, the “User LGIAs”) and, anticipates becoming a User hereunder in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. H. The Users will have the rights provided herein with respect to interconnection and transmission service across the Gen-Tie Line to the Point of Interconnection, and certain other rights as provided herein (the “Interconnection Rights”). I. Interconnection Provider owns, or has certain rights to use, the Gen-Tie Facilities. J. By virtue of the Service Agreement entered into of even date herewith BF1 is a User as of the date hereof, further confirmed by its execution of this Agreement on the signature page following the end of Section 16, and the Interconnection Provider anticipates that BF2 and BF3 may hereafter become Users in accordance with this Agreement. K. Each User desires to obtain the Services from the Interconnection Provider in order to deliver electricity from its Project to the Point of Interconnection. L. Interconnection Provider and each User desires to set forth their respective rights and obligations with respect to the Projects and the Interconnection Rights and Gen-Tie Facilities. M. The Parties entered into that certain Master Interconnection Services Agreement, dated December 19, 2023 (the “Original MISA”), and subsequently entered into that First Amendment to the Master Interconnection Services Agreement, dated December 30, 2024 (the “First Amendment”). The Parties desire to amend and restate the Original MISA to incorporate the amendments set forth in the First Amendment as set forth herein as of the Execution Date. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing Recitals, the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows: 1. DEFINITIONS 1.1 Definitions. Unless otherwise noted, capitalized terms not defined in the body of this Agreement have the following meanings. “Affiliate” means, with respect to any Party, any Person directly or indirectly controlling, controlled by or under common control with such Party. The term “control” and correlative terms includes the possession, directly or indirectly and whether acting alone or in conjunction with others, of the authority to direct or cause the direction of the management or policies of a Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities, by contract, or otherwise. “Agreement” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. “BF1” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. “BF2” and “BF3” each have the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “BF1 LGIA” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “BF1 Substation” means the high-voltage electric substation to be located on the portion of the Premises described on Exhibit A-1. “BF2 LGIA” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “BF2/BF3 Shared Substation” means the high-voltage electric substation to be located on the Premises. “BF3 FNTP Date” means the date on which FNTP is issued by BF3 with respect to the BF3 project. “BF3 LGIA” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “BF3 Gen-Tie Payment” means the payment to be made by or on behalf of BF3 as provided in Section 6.3.5.2 of the Purchase Agreement. “Business Day” means any means any day other than a Saturday, a Sunday or a day on which commercial banks in New York, New York are required or authorized to be closed. “CAISO” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “Capacity Log” means the form attached hereto as Exhibit B, as updated from time to time as applicable, showing the Reserved Capacity and Cost Percentage of each User applicable to allocation of costs and expenses hereunder, except for those costs and expenses as to which a different allocation is specified on Exhibit C. “Casualty Event” means an event that causes all or a portion of the Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets to be damaged, destroyed or rendered unfit for normal use for any reason whatsoever. “Condemnation Event” means any compulsory transfer or taking or transfer under threat of compulsory transfer or taking of all or a material part of the Premises, Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets by any Governmental Authority or entity acting under power of eminent domain. “Confidential Information” with respect to a given Disclosing Party and the respective Receiving Party, means, collectively and individually, all data, materials and information (including software, data, technology, know-how, trade secrets, processes, ideas, inventions (whether patentable or not), prototypes, schematics, design plans, drawings, pricing information, customer and service provider lists, business arrangements, business information, financial information, financial results, technical information, analyses, forecasts, compilations, studies, contracts, agreements, and planning or strategy information) provided by or on behalf of a Party (each Party in such capacity, a “Disclosing Party”) to the other Party (each Party in such capacity, a “Receiving Party”) or the Receiving Party’s Representatives, or to which the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives are given access by or on behalf of the Disclosing Party, whether verbally or in written or electronic form, related to the Disclosing Party, any Project, the Gen-Tie Facilities, the Managed Assets, the Premises or the Users in connection with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Confidential Information under this Agreement does not include any information that: (A) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is now publicly available, or that later becomes publicly available through no action by the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives in violation of this Agreement, (B) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is already in the possession of the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives and is not subject to a confidentiality or fiduciary obligation at the time of the information’s disclosure under this Agreement, (C) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is lawfully received from any source other than the Disclosing Party or the Disclosing Party’s Representatives under circumstances not involving, to the Receiving Party’s knowledge, a breach of any fiduciary or confidentiality obligation, or (D) the Receiving Party can demonstrate is independently developed by or for the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party’s Representatives without reference to, or the use of, any portion of the Confidential Information. “Consent of the MA Users” means the written consent of Users that hold more than fifty percent (50%) of the aggregate Undivided Interests in the applicable Managed Assets; provided that, to the extent that a particular decision requiring Consent of the MA Users would have a materially adverse effect on any User’s project that is disproportionately worse for such Project in comparison to the effect on the other Projects that use the Managed Assets, then the written consent of the User that owns such Project shall also be required, except if the dissimilar treatment is required by Prudent Industry Practices. “Consent of the Users” means the written consent of Users that hold more than fifty percent (50%) of the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Users whose Projects are connected and Energized; provided that, to the extent that a particular decision requiring Consent of the Users would have a materially adverse effect on any User’s project that is disproportionately worse for such Project in comparison to the effect on the other Projects, then the written consent of the User that owns such Project shall also be required except if the dissimilar treatment is required by Prudent Industry Practices. “Cost Percentage” is a fraction, with respect to a User, where (a) the numerator is the Nameplate Capacity of such User’s Project or Projects with respect to the Gen-Tie Facilities or each Segment of the Managed Assets, as the case may be, and (b) the denominator is the Nameplate Capacity of all of the current Users’ Projects utilizing the Gen-Tie Facilities or such Segment of the Managed Assets, as the case may be. Any Person becoming a New User under this Agreement will be assigned a Cost Percentage with respect to the Gen-Tie Facilities and the applicable Managed Assets based on an adjusted aggregated capacity that utilizes the Gen-Tie Facilities and such Segment of the Managed Assets that includes the New User’s Project Nameplate Capacity. Upon the admittance of a New User, the Cost Percentage of all of the existing Users will be similarly adjusted by the new denominator (if applicable) representing the new aggregated Nameplate Capacity of all Users’ Projects. The Cost Percentage shall be determined and applied with respect to the Gen-Tie Facilities and the applicable Segments of the Managed Assets as specified in Exhibit C, as such Exhibit C shall be updated by Interconnection Provider to include each New User by notice to the Users from time to time; provided that notwithstanding anything in this definition of “Cost Percentage”, the Cost Percentage or cost allocations applicable to specified payment obligations hereunder shall be determined as provided in Exhibit C. “Default Rate” means a rate per annum equal to the lesser of (a) a varying rate per annum equal to the sum of (i) the three (3) month LIBOR as published in The Wall Street Journal, with adjustments in that varying rate to be made on the same date as any change in that rate is so published, plus (ii) two percent (2%) per annum, and (b) the maximum rate permitted by Law. If LIBOR is no longer available, then the Default Rate shall utilize a successor rate or reasonable replacement rate, as selected by Interconnection Provider. “Disclosing Party” has the meaning set forth in the definition of “Confidential Information.” “Eligible Customer” means any Person that owns or operates an ESR or electricity generating facility that is generating or injecting or will generate or inject electricity for sale or resale, that is or previously was an affiliate of Interconnection Provider (as defined in 18 C.F.R. 366.1) and that has entered into an interconnection agreement with the Transmission Owner and CAISO for interconnection service at the Point of Interconnection using the Gen-Tie Facilities. A Person is not an Eligible Customer if it serves load. “Emergency” shall mean any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of Interconnection Provider or a User, that may arise that requires immediate action and which constitutes a serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of Persons or property, that may materially interfere with the safe, economical or environmentally sound operation of the Gen-Tie Facilities, the Managed Assets or any Project, or that would violate any applicable Law, Governmental Approvals, the User LGIAs, or any Premises Documents. “Energized” shall refer to a state of completion where electrical current begins to flow. “Electric Storage Resource” or “ESR” means a resource capable of receiving electric energy from the grid or from an associated Project’s generating facilities and storing it for later injection of electricity to the grid. “Environmental Laws” means all Laws relating to the protection of the environment, health or safety or the use, generation, release, treatment, storage, disposal or exposure to Hazardous Materials, including the Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation and Liability Act of 1980, as amended by the Superfund Amendments and Reauthorization Act of 1986; the Clean Water Act; the Resource, Conservation and Recovery Act of 1976; the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970; and the Clean Air Act, all as amended, and equivalent State of California laws and regulations. “Event of Default” has the meaning set forth in Section 14.1. “Execution Date” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. “EWG” means an “exempt wholesale generator,” as such term is defined in Section 1262(6) of the Public Utility Holding Company Act of 2005 and the FERC’s rules at 18 C.F.R. § 366.1. “FERC” means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. “Financing Party” means, with respect to each User, the agent or lead bank and any other financial institutions (or associated lenders, collateral agents and administrative agents) that are party or a potential or prospective party to a loan agreement, hedge agreement, tax equity financing documents (including through a partnership flip arrangement or other similar financing) or other debt, equity or other type of financing or investment instrument with such User, including a sale-leaseback. “First Amendment” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “FNTP” means the notice issued by the owner of a Project to a contractor authorizing such contractor to commence the full scope of work to engineer, procure and construct the applicable Project. “Force Majeure” means acts of God or any other casualty or occurrence, condition, event or circumstance of any kind or nature that (i) is not reasonably within the affected Party’s control, (ii) was not foreseeable, or if foreseeable, could not have been avoided by reasonable measures by the affected Party, and (iii) prevents, hinders or delays the performance by the affected Party, including national or regional strikes, slow downs or labor difficulties that are not specific to or solely directed to the affected Party or any of its subcontractors, fires, floods, earthquakes, explosions, natural disasters, pandemic, or other hazards, acts of a Governmental Authority, acts of public enemies, riots, civil commotions, insurrection, or war. Force Majeure expressly does not include any delay in performing or failure of performance of any contractual provision by any Party (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); late delivery or breakage of equipment or materials (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); or economic hardship. “Gen-Tie Facilities” means the interconnection and transmission facilities and related equipment owned by the Interconnection Provider to the Point of Interconnection as described as “Gen-Tie Facilities (Interconnection Provider)” and identified in blue in Exhibit A-1. A diagram of the Gen-Tie Facilities is attached at Exhibit A-1. Gen-Tie Facilities do not include Managed Assets. “Gen-Tie Facilities Representative” has the meaning set forth in Section 5.2. “Governmental Approval” means any: (a) permit, license, certificate, concession, approval, consent, ratification, permission, clearance, confirmation, exemption, waiver, franchise, certification, designation, rating, registration, variance, qualification, accreditation or authorization issued, granted, given or otherwise made available by or under the authority of any Governmental Authority or pursuant to any Law, and any grading, building, or conditional use permits affecting the applicable real property and in effect with respect to the Projects, the Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets, or any part of them, pursuant to any Law and issued or required to be obtained for the construction, ownership or operation of any Project, the Gen-Tie Facilities or the Managed Assets, or (b) right under any contract with any Governmental Authority. “Governmental Authority” means any court, tribunal, authority, agency, commission, official or other instrumentality, including regulatory authorities and bodies, of the United States or any state, county, city or other political subdivision; any quasi-governmental regulatory authority, such as NERC or CAISO, acting under delegated authority; any arbitrator; or any judicial or quasi-judicial tribunal of competent jurisdiction. “Hazardous Materials” means any hazardous or toxic substance or waste, pollutant or contaminant as defined under applicable Environmental Laws, including petroleum products, asbestos, polychlorinated biphenyls and radioactive materials. “Interconnection Expenses” has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2.1. “Interconnection Provider” means 59TC 8me LLC or its successor hereunder. “Interconnection Rights” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “Landowner” means the county, municipality, or fee simple owner from which each User and the Interconnection Company received their right to locate Gen Tie Facilities, Project Specific Assets and/or Managed Assets on the Premises. “Laws” means any applicable constitutional provisions, statutes, acts, codes, laws, rules, regulations, ordinances, orders, decrees, rulings, judgments or decisions of a Governmental Authority or arbitral body. “Liabilities” means any and all claims, actions, debts, losses, liabilities, damages, expenses, awards, judgments, settlement payments, fines, penalties, costs, royalties, assessments (tax or otherwise), proceedings, deficiencies or obligations, whether civil or criminal, including those arising out of any investigation, action, claim, settlement, compromise, judgment or award, by any private party or Governmental Authority, of any nature, whether known or unknown, absolute, accrued, contingent or otherwise, and whether due or to become due, and whether or not resulting from third party claims, and any out-of-pocket costs and expenses (including court costs and fees, and reasonable legal counsels’, accountants’, or other fees and expenses) incurred in defending against or investigating any of the same. “Liens” means all mortgages, deeds of trust, liens, debentures, security interests, pledges, conditional sale contracts, proceedings, judgment liens, orders, rights of first refusal, charges and other encumbrances or restrictions of any kind, whether recorded or unrecorded. “Loss Event” means a Casualty Event or a Condemnation Event. “MA User” means each User that holds an Undivided Interests in Managed Assets. “Managed Assets” means those assets used in the operation of more than one Project (including interconnection and transmission) that are used by one or more Users, as specified in Exhibit A-2, and that are managed (but not owned) by Interconnection Provider for purposes of effecting interconnection service for the applicable Projects. For purposes of clarity, Managed Assets are not Gen-Tie Facilities under this Agreement. “MISA” has the meaning set forth in the Preamble. “MW” means megawatt (alternating current unless otherwise specified). “Nameplate Capacity” means, as to a Project, the total net output capacity of such Project, including the ESR, if applicable, as measured in alternating current (in MW) at the Point of Interconnection, consistent with the description of the ESR in the corresponding User LGIA, and which shall not exceed the total net output capacity provided under such LGIA. The Nameplate Capacity shall be identified in Exhibit B and in the respective Service Agreements. “NERC” means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation. “NERC CIP Requirements” means the Critical Infrastructure Protection standards as established by NERC from time to time. “Net Revenue Loss” means the sum of (a) the product of (i) the MWh of electricity that would have been produced by the applicable Project (based on the CAISO eligible intermittent resource protocol forecast adjusted for Project availability, or if such forecast is unavailable or inaccurate, the best available weather, historical, availability or other pertinent data) during the applicable period, and (ii) the price such electricity would have been sold by the affected User under such User’s power purchase agreement had the electricity been produced, or if such User has no power purchase agreement, then at the Resource-Specific Settlement Interval LMP (as defined in the CAISO Tariff) for electricity during such period, (b) if the User is eligible to receive renewable energy credits, including those granted pursuant to law, regulation, certification, markets, trading, off-set, private transaction, renewable portfolio standards or voluntary programs (“RECs”), the dollar value for the RECs that would have been payable to the affected User based on the price that would have been payable under any contract for the sale of the RECs, plus any related damages or costs resulting from the failure to deliver and sell such RECs, or if and to the extent applicable, the average price per MWh of RECs of two valid seller price quotes for lots of not less than 5,000 MWhs of comparable RECs from nationally recognized REC brokers; provided such User is not otherwise compensated for RECs as part of subsection (a) above, (c) the value of any applicable tax credits that would have been available based on the electricity that would have been produced by the applicable Project (determined as provided in clause (a) above), (d) substantiated lost revenues resulting from the Project being unable to provide capacity, (e) any penalties or liquidated damages assessed against such User for failing to produce electricity such User was contractually obligated to produce, grossed up on an after-tax basis and taking into account applicable state and local taxes, and (f) if the Project is (or includes) an ESR then, in addition to the foregoing, Net Revenue Loss will be calculated to reflect (x) any mitigating impacts of storage capacity available to store energy that would otherwise have been delivered to the Point of Interconnection during the relevant period, and (y) substantiated lost revenues resulting from the ESR being unable to deliver energy or provide capacity or ancillary services during the relevant period. “New User” means an Eligible Customer (other than BF1) that has entered into a Service Agreement subject to and in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. “Original MISA” has the meaning set forth in the Recitals. “Other Indemnified Parties” has the meaning set forth in Section 11.2. “Outside Date” means the earlier of (a) the date that the BF3 LGIA is no longer in full force and effect, and (b) the date that the Sellers’ Parent Guaranty is no longer in full force and effect and the BF3 Gen-Tie Payment has not been paid in full. “Parties” and “Party” means, individually and collectively, as the context requires, the Interconnection Provider or any User(s). “Permitted Liens” means (a) liens imposed by law securing the charges, claims, demands or levies of mechanics, materialmen, carriers, warehousemen and other like Persons which (i) are incurred in connection with the interconnection of one or more Projects to the Gen-Tie Facilities, or the construction, operation or maintenance of the Gen-Tie Facilities or any Managed Assets, and (ii) secure obligations (A) that are not yet due, or (B)(1) are being contested in good faith and by appropriate proceedings diligently pursued, which proceedings have the effect of preventing the foreclosure, forfeiture or sale of the property or assets subject to such lien, (2) for which adequate reserves (in the good faith judgment of the Users) have been established in accordance with GAAP or which are secured by bonds or other security reasonably satisfactory to the Users, and (3) as to which the property or assets subject to such lien is not yet subject to foreclosure, sale or loss on account thereof, (b) liens or deposits to secure the performance of bids, tenders, trade contracts, trade payables, and leases (other than for the repayment of borrowed money) incurred in the ordinary course of business, (c) pledges or deposits to secure regulatory or statutory obligations, surety and appeal bonds, performance bonds and other obligations of a like nature incurred in the ordinary course of business securing the payment of amounts not yet due and payable or amounts being contested in good faith and by appropriate proceedings, (d) all exceptions listed in the title policy with respect to the Premises or other land use restrictions that do not impair the use or value of the Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets, in each case whether now or hereafter in existence, (e) mortgages against the fee interest of the real property subject to a Premises Document, provided that (except with respect to mortgages in favor of a Financing Party), in a written, recorded document to the benefit of the Interconnection Provider, the mortgagee thereof shall have subordinated its interest to the interest of Interconnection Provider under the applicable Premises Document or shall have agreed not to foreclose or otherwise disturb the use or possession of the Premises by Interconnection Provider or any User under such Premises Document in the absence of a default by the Interconnection Provider continuing beyond the applicable grace period, (f) Liens and any right of setoff in favor of a bank or other financial institution arising by operation of applicable Laws or in the ordinary course of business encumbering deposits held by such bank or financial institution, (g) Liens for taxes not yet due or as provided in Section 6.2, (h) with respect to Users, Liens in favor of a Financing Party with respect to a User’s interest in this Agreement or with respect to a User’s Undivided Interest or User Premises Interests, as provided in Section 5.6.2 and Section 6.10, and (i) judgment Liens that do not involve immediate risk of forfeiture of any portion of or interest in the Gen-Tie Facilities and, within ten (10) Business Days of their existence or after the entry thereof, are being contested in good faith and by appropriate proceedings, and adequate reserves with respect thereto are maintained on the books of the applicable Person in accordance with GAAP or the Lien is covered by insurance, bonds or other security reasonably satisfactory to the Users. “Person” means any individual, partnership, joint stock company, corporation, limited liability company, trust, unincorporated association or joint venture, Governmental Authority, or other entity. “Point of Interconnection” has the meaning set forth in the BF1 LGIA, the BF2 LGIA, and the BF3 LGIA. “Premises” means (a) the real property in which the Interconnection Provider has a leasehold, easement, franchise or license interest in connection with the Gen-Tie Facilities, (b) the real property in which BF1 has a leasehold or easement interest in connection with the BF1 Substation, (c) the real property in which BF2 or BF3 may hereafter have a leasehold or easement interest in connection with the BF2/BF3 Shared Substation and associated 230 kV line extension between the BF1 Substation and the BF2/BF3 Shared Substation, and (d) the BF1 Substation access road described in Exhibit A-2 as Segment 2, all as further described in Exhibit F. “Premises Documents” means those documents that provide Interconnection Provider with the rights and authority to construct, own, and operate the Gen-Tie Facilities on the Premises or provide Users with sufficient rights to access the Premises and to locate the Managed Assets and Project Specific Assets on the Premises. The Premises Documents are listed on Exhibit G. Exhibit G may be updated from time to time as needed by the Interconnection Provider without an amendment to the Agreement and shall include an agreement regarding the sharing of permits entered into by the Parties to the extent applicable to the Premises. “Project(s)” means, in the case of each User, its solar photovoltaic facility or ESR, whether or not associated with its solar photovoltaic facility in whole or in part (inclusive of modules, inverters, and associated infrastructure) used to generate or store and discharge electric energy, provide capacity, or provide ancillary services or, in the case of the Interconnection Provider, all or any portion of the Gen-Tie Facilities. “Project Site(s)” means the real property upon which each User’s Project is located. “Project Specific Assets” means, for each Project, any of the assets that are owned by a single User, used in the operation of such User’s Project, located on the Premises at a point before the Gen-Tie Facilities, including the portion of the collector system for the Project located on the Premises and Project specific meters, switches, current transformers, potential transformers, step-up transformers, transformer bays reclosers, switches, VAR compensation, and the agreements and contractual arrangements comprising the User Premises Interests applicable to the installation and operation of such assets on the Premises. A non-exhaustive list of the Project Specific Assets is in Exhibit A-2. For the avoidance of doubt, the Project Specific Assets are not included in the Gen-Tie Facilities. Fencing installed on the Premises around the perimeter of the Project Sites will be constructed, owned, operated and maintained by the applicable User and shall not be Project Specific Assets. “Prudent Industry Practices” means any of the practices, methods, and standards of care, skill, safety and diligence, as the same may change from time to time, but applied in light of the facts known at the time, as are generally applied or utilized under comparable circumstances by reasonably experienced and prudent professionals in respect of the design, development, construction, commissioning, SERVICE AGREEMENTS Interconnection Provider shall, subject to the requirements of Section 6.13, offer a Service Agreement to each Eligible Customer specifically identified in Section 6.13 that has requested interconnection and transmission service across the Gen-Tie Facilities by submitting a written application for such services to Interconnection Provider. Interconnection Provider shall promptly notify each existing User of its receipt of any such application from an Eligible Customer. From the Service Commencement Date and during the Service Term specified in a User’s Service Agreement, such User shall purchase, and the Interconnection Provider shall provide, interconnection service and firm transmission service over the Gen-Tie Facilities pursuant to the terms and conditions of this Agreement (the “Services”). Each Service Agreement entitles its respective User to a reservation of capacity on, and firm transmission service over, the Gen-Tie Facilities in an amount specified in such User’s Service Agreement, which may be in an amount up to but not exceeding the capacity specified in the applicable User LGIA (the “Reserved Capacity”); provided that the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Users and the aggregate Nameplate Capacity of all Projects shall not, and the Interconnection Provider shall not permit the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Users and the aggregate Nameplate Capacity of all Projects to, exceed 1150 MWac. Interconnection Provider may update the form of Service Agreement as needed from time to time to address construction, operations, regulatory or maintenance issues. 3. GEN-TIE FACILITIES 3.1 Gen-Tie Facilities. The Interconnection Provider has caused or will cause the procurement, installation and construction of, as applicable, the Gen-Tie Facilities prior to the first User’s Service Commencement Date. Pursuant to and subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the interconnection and transmission services provided by Interconnection Provider under this Agreement shall entitle each User to firm transmission service over the Gen-Tie Facilities pursuant to the User LGIAs. 3.2 Premises. 3.2.1 As of the date hereof or the date of its Service Agreement, as applicable, each User has separately obtained from the Landowner or the Interconnection Provider all User Premises Interests required to construct its Managed Assets and Project Specific Assets. Without limiting the rights of the Interconnection Provider or any other User with respect to its User Premises Interest, if a User later determines that it requires an additional nonexclusive easement to construct Project Specific Assets, then Interconnection Provider, to the extent that it has the right to do so under the Premises Documents to which it is party, shall grant to such User, for the benefit of and appurtenant to such User’s a non-exclusive subeasement over, under, across and through the applicable portion of the Premises for the purpose of constructing, operating and maintaining Project Specific Assets and Managed Assets on the Premises (subject to the provisions of Section 3.4 and Section 6.7), including overhead transmission lines and related facilities, and ingress and egress access thereto, if, as and to the extent that (a) such rights are granted to Interconnection Provider pursuant to the Premises Documents; (b) Interconnection Provider is permitted pursuant to the terms of the Premises Documents to grant such subeasement; (c) such subeasement is reasonably required by such User in connection with the interconnection of such User’s Project; (d) such subeasement does not interfere with, limit or otherwise adversely affect the Interconnection Provider’s or any User’s use of, interest in or costs and expense in connection with (unless the requesting User has agreed in writing to pay such costs and expenses on terms reasonably satisfactory to the affected Users), the affected portion of the Premises, and (e) without limitation, the User to which the subeasement is granted assumes a reasonably allocated portion of the cost, expenses and other obligations under the applicable Premises Documents. Each User shall keep, observe and perform, or cause to be kept, observed and performed, all the terms and conditions of the Premises Documents and any applicable Governmental Approvals, to the extent attributable to such User’s Project Specific Assets, including all applicable CAISO requirements and NERC requirements (which shall include the NERC CIP Requirements), and all other activities on or with respect to the Premises or obligations with respect thereto and shall refrain from performing any act or causing any condition that is not within its rights under the Premises Documents or the applicable Governmental Approvals or as to which it is prohibited from performing or causing under the terms, covenants and conditions of the Premises Documents, the Governmental Approvals or this Agreement. Additionally, subject to the other requirements and limitations in this Section 3.2.1, Interconnection Provider and each User shall, upon request of a User, reasonably cooperate with such requesting User to support such requesting User obtaining rights under any Premises Documents to which the Interconnection Provider or such User is party to locate Project Specific Assets within the Premises, including by directly granting rights to such requesting User under such Premises Documents to which it is party (to the extent permitted pursuant to the terms of the applicable Premises Documents), or by reasonably assisting such requesting User in such requesting User’s applications or requests to obtain direct rights from the grantor under the applicable Premises Documents. 3.2.2 The Interconnection Provider, if applicable, and the Users shall timely execute the necessary instruments to effect the grant of rights to the applicable User as necessary to operate the applicable Project, as provided in and subject to Section 3.2.1. 3.2.3 Notwithstanding the provisions of Section 3.2.1, any amounts due under the terms of the Premises Documents and Governmental Approvals (except in each case to the extent incurred and paid for directly by a User, including in connection with the User Premises Interests, which amounts shall be for the account of and be paid directly by the applicable Users to the Landowner, Interconnection Provider, or other User as applicable), shall be paid by the Interconnection Provider, subject to reimbursement by the Users in accordance with Section 4. 3.3 Access. Subject to the provisions of Section 3.4 and Section 6.7, each User and its Representatives shall have access to the Premises to the extent of and in accordance with its User Premises Interests for the installation, maintenance, or repairs of its Project Specific Assets. The Interconnection Provider, each User or each User’s Representatives shall follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the Interconnection Provider and shall comply with all applicable Premises Documents, Laws, and Governmental Approvals, including all applicable CAISO requirements, NERC requirements (including NERC CIP Requirements), when on the Premises and at all times as applicable to the Gen-Tie Facilities, Managed Assets or Project Specific Assets. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Gen-Tie Facilities, Managed Assets or Project Specific Assets to respond to such Emergency, but the User shall provide notice of access to Interconnection Provider and the other affected Users as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter (which shall be no more than twenty-four (24) hours after access). As to each Managed Asset and Project Specific Assets, each MA User or owner thereof, as applicable, shall promptly provide to the other MA Users all data and other relevant information requested and reasonably required to evidence compliance with its obligations in this Section 3.3. 3.4 No Interference, Cooperation and Over-Burdening. A User’s use of the Gen-Tie Facilities, any applicable Managed Assets and the Premises and the operation of its Project, shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Users of their respective rights to use the Gen-Tie Facilities, applicable Managed Assets or the Premises or the operation of their respective Projects, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each User shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the other Users’ use of the Gen-Tie Facilities, any applicable Managed Assets and the Premises for the benefit of the Projects in accordance with this Agreement. No User will use or permit the use of the Gen-Tie Facilities, the Managed Assets, the Project Specific Assets located on the Premises or the Premises in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, adversely affect any other Project or that would jeopardize, limit, condition or increase the cost of the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Gen-Tie Facilities, any applicable Managed Assets or the Premises or any Governmental Approval as to any Project or as to the Gen-Tie Facilities, any applicable Managed Assets or the Premises, nor otherwise conduct or permit to be conducted operations on its Project Site which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Gen-Tie Facilities, any applicable Managed Assets or the Premises. All incremental costs and expenses associated with a User interconnecting a Project into the Gen-Tie Facilities or the Managed Assets shall be for the account of, and paid for, by such User. 3.5 Additional Facilities. Except for Managed Assets and Project Specific Assets as provided in this Agreement, no User shall construct, install or place any additional facilities or equipment within the Premises. 3.6 Conditions to Connecting Projects to the Gen-Tie Facilities. Any User connecting its Project (or expanding its Project to include an ESR) to the Gen-Tie Facilities shall (a) not interfere with the use or access by the other Users of the Gen-Tie Facilities, except to the extent necessary during the installation, repair, or replacement of the Gen-Tie Facilities, (b) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak or low solar insolation period any required disconnection of the Gen-Tie Facilities to conduct construction or interconnection activities to minimize the impact on the Projects of the other Users, (c) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice to Interconnection Provider and each User of commencement of such construction or interconnection activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (d) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice to Interconnection Provider and each User of any planned outages, and the durations thereof, of the Gen-Tie Facilities that would result in a disconnection or interruption of another User’s Project, (e) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes requested by another User in such construction, interconnection, disconnection or interruption, (f) be responsible for obtaining and complying with any necessary Governmental Approvals required for such activities and providing documentary evidence of such Governmental Approvals to the Users and Interconnection Provider, (g) compensate each other User for its Net Revenue Loss due to an outage or disconnection of such already-connected User’s Project, and (h) deliver to Interconnection Provider a reliability impact study in compliance with NERC FAC-001 within 45 days of signing the Service Agreement . Any User connecting its own Project (or expanding its Project to include an ESR) to the Gen-Tie Facilities shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Users from all Liabilities, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred (other than Net Revenue Loss resulting from outage or disconnection as provided in clause (g) of the preceding sentence), related to such construction or installation activities, but, without limitation of the foregoing, such installing User may seek reimbursement for such indemnified costs from insurance carried by the indemnifying User to the extent such insurance provides coverage for such indemnified costs. 3.7 Conditions to Connecting Projects to the Managed Assets. Any User connecting its Project (or expanding its Project to include an ESR) to the Managed Assets shall (a) obtain the written permission of each owner of the Managed Asset, (b) not interfere with the use of or access to the Managed Assets by the relevant Users, except to the extent provided herein during the installation, repair, or replacement of the Managed Assets, (c) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak or low solar insolation period any required disconnection of the Managed Assets to conduct construction activities to minimize the impact on the Projects of the other Users, (d) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice to Interconnection Provider and each relevant User of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (e) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice to Interconnection Provider and each relevant User of any planned outages, and the durations thereof, of the Managed Assets that would result in a disconnection of another User’s Project, (f) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction required by another User, (g) be responsible for obtaining and complying with any necessary Governmental Approvals required for such connection and providing documentary evidence of such Governmental Approvals to the Users and Interconnection Provider, and (h) compensate each other User for its Net Revenue Loss as a result of an outage or disconnection of such already-connected User’s Project. Any User connecting its own Project (or expanding its Project to include an ESR) to the Managed Assets shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Users from all Liabilities, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred, related to such construction or installation activities, but, without limitation of its obligations herein, such installing User may seek reimbursement in whole or part for such indemnified costs from insurance that it carries to the extent such insurance provides coverage for such indemnified costs. 3.8 Partial Conveyance of Co-tenancy Interests in Managed Assets. Effective upon (a) the completion of construction or installation of each component of the Managed Assets on the Premises, or (b) at any time thereafter that any New Users join this Agreement and take an interest in such Managed Assets, which construction and installation shall have been performed on and be subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth in this Agreement and in the applicable Premises Agreements, and as to which the New Users have obtained the prior FERC authorization for conveyances that occur after the applicable Managed Assets are energized, if applicable, the User constructing or installing (or causing the construction or installation of) such component of the Managed Assets shall grant, sell, transfer and convey an undivided ownership interest in and to such component of the Managed Assets constructed or installed (or caused to be constructed or installed) by such User to one or more other Users, in each case in proportion to such transferee’s Cost Percentage, subject to the payment by such respective transferee User to such User of the payment for construction costs (including financing costs) of such Managed Assets in proportion to its respective ownership interests in such Managed Assets as provided in Section 5.4.1, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW, while at the same time reserving to itself an undivided ownership interest in and to such component of the applicable Managed Assets in proportion to its Cost Percentage. The intent of the foregoing is that the applicable Users shall acquire and hold an undivided tenancy in common interest in each component of the Managed Assets in the proportion to its Cost Percentage so as to provide for the joint ownership of the Managed Assets (along with all appurtenant rights) by the Users subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The foregoing undivided tenancy in common interest of each User in the Managed Assets may be referred to from time to time in this Agreement as an “Undivided Interest”. For the avoidance of doubt, as to any New User, the conveyance and terms of this Section 3.8 shall not become effective until the conditions specified in Section 6.13 have been satisfied and the applicable Service Commencement Date for the New User has occurred. At such time as a New User obtains an undivided interest in any Managed Assets, it shall pay to the other holders of undivided interests in such Managed Assets, pro rata, its allocated payment with respect to such Managed Assets. Upon the termination or withdrawal of a MA User as a User or the permanent disconnection from the Gen-Tie Facilities of such MA User’s Project in accordance with this Agreement, such MA User shall convey all of its Undivided Interest to the other MA Users in proportion to their Cost Percentages in effect as of such termination, withdrawal or disconnection. 4. Except as specifically set forth in this Agreement, each User shall be solely responsible for its costs, expenses and Liabilities relating to its Project, the User LGIA to which it is party and Project Specific Assets, including all costs, expenses and Liabilities arising from acquiring, designing, installing, constructing, using, operating, maintaining and repairing its Project Specific Assets. Each User shall be responsible for all Liabilities arising from such User’s actions or inactions in violation of this Agreement. 4.2 Interconnection Expenses. 4.2.1 The Users each shall be responsible for and shall reimburse the Interconnection Provider (in accordance with Section 4.3) for Liabilities arising under or relating to the following (collectively, the “Interconnection Expenses”), in proportion to its respective Cost Percentage for the Gen-Tie Facilities unless otherwise specified: (a) as to each User, the User LGIA Expenses described in clause (a) of the definition of “User LGIA Expenses”; (b) any fees, costs, expenses and Liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Interconnection Provider for or in connection with the use, maintenance, operation, repair, reclamation or inspection of the Gen-Tie Facilities, including the User LGIA Expenses described in clause (b) of the definition of “User LGIA Expenses”; (c) the fees, costs, expenses and Liabilities arising under or in connection with any Premises Documents or the use, maintenance, operation, repair, and inspection of the Premises (except to the extent such costs are incurred directly by or otherwise allocated directly to a User); (d) any fees, costs, expenses or Liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Interconnection Provider hereunder (including Liabilities arising under any Governmental Approval); (e) an annual management fee for the benefit of Interconnection Provider in the total amount of $10.00; and (f) the fees, costs, expenses and Liabilities payable or incurred by the Interconnection Provider to a third party under any Shared Facilities MSA. 4.2.2 The costs and expenses of any Project Specific Assets and the connection and integration of Project Specific Assets with any Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets (including any design, procurement, construction, tax, or installation costs) shall not be considered Interconnection Expenses hereunder. The Users also acknowledge that modification of their Project or amendment of a User LGIA may cause costs to another User’s Project, directly or indirectly because of required modifications to the Gen-Tie Facilities, Managed Assets or another User’s Project Specific Assets. Each User individually, shall be responsible for timely payment of any fees, costs, taxes, expenses or liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Interconnection Provider or another User (i) for the construction, use, maintenance, operation, repair, and inspection of any incremental equipment added to the Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets for the purpose of accommodating the interconnection of a new User’s Project as well as (ii) any incremental additional equipment required to be added to another User’s Project to facilitate additional short circuit contribution costs, centralized remedial action tripping scheme costs, or other equipment or programming, in each case to the extent required to accommodate the interconnection or operation of a new User’s Project, modification of an existing Project (such as a change in inverter) or to the extent such change is triggered by an amendment to or other modification to an individual User LGIA. The foregoing costs described in this Section 4.2.2 will not be considered Interconnection Expenses, and Interconnection Provider may directly assign costs under this Section 4.2 to specific Users as appropriate. 4.2.3 The aggregate of the Service Fees that would be applicable proportionally to all Users will initially be borne by BF1. BF1 may elect, at its sole and exclusive option, to continue to make such payments in full, or alternatively to have a portion of the Service Fee corresponding to any or all New User’s Cost Percentage to be allocated to such New Users as an Interconnection Expense, which fee shall be payable monthly commencing on the second anniversary of the date that the New User’s Service Agreement becomes effective; provided that, if the BF3 Gen-Tie Payment has been paid in full in accordance with the Purchase Agreement and BF3 subsequently becomes a New User, then no portion of the Service Fee shall be allocated to BF3 and provided further, that notwithstanding the foregoing, the payment of the Service Fee payable by BF3, if applicable, shall be as shown in Exhibit C and shall commence as of the BF3 FNTP Date. 4.3 Invoicing; Late Payments. No later than the first day of each calendar month, beginning with a User’s respective Service Commencement Date, the Interconnection Provider shall invoice such User for its respective portions of the Interconnection Expenses for the prior month. Interconnection Provider’s invoice shall include a detailed breakdown of the Interconnection Expenses and each User’s share of the Interconnection Expenses, along with instructions for making payment to Interconnection Provider. The Users shall make all payments to Interconnection Provider under this Section 4.3 within thirty (30) days of receipt of such invoice by wire transfer of immediately available funds to an account specified by Interconnection Provider. All sums not paid within thirty (30) days after receipt of Interconnection Provider’s invoice shall thereafter bear interest at the Default Rate. Each User will have the right to audit, and receive supporting documentation for, any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by such User under this Agreement. If there is a dispute as to any amount invoiced by Interconnection Provider, the Users shall pay all amounts not in dispute in accordance with this Section 4.3. The Users shall pay any disputed amount ultimately determined as payable with interest thereon at the Default Rate accruing from the date of receipt of the Interconnection Provider’s disputed invoice. 5. USE OF GEN-TIE FACILITIES AND MANAGED ASSETS 5.1 Use by Projects. Subject to the other requirements of this Agreement, each User shall have the right to interconnection and transmission service over the Gen-Tie Facilities on a firm basis to the extent of the Reserved Capacity set forth in such User’s Service Agreement. The Users shall share line losses across the Gen Tie Facilities and each Segment of the Managed Assets pro rata based on the ratio of each Project’s Reserved Capacity to the aggregate Reserved Capacity of all Projects, as adjusted by dynamic line loading calculations, the contributions of each Project to those calculations, and other considerations in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices. Each User that holds an Undivided Interest in a Managed Asset will be able to use the Managed Asset consistent with its interests shown in Exhibit C. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, each User separately owns and shall own the electrical energy, capacity, and ancillary services generated by, or associated with, its Project. 5.2 Gen-Tie Facilities Representatives. On or promptly following a User’s Service Commencement Date, such User shall, by written notice to the other Users and Interconnection Provider, designate an individual (the “Gen-Tie Facilities Representative”), who will have authority to bind the User in all matters concerning this Agreement, to communicate on a day-to-day basis with each other User and to direct Interconnection Provider regarding construction, operations, compliance and maintenance issues. Each User may change its Gen-Tie Facilities Representative at any time and from time to time by prior written notice to the other Users and Interconnection Provider and updating such designation in its Service Agreement. 5.3 Liens. (I) the Interconnection Provider shall not, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any Lien on the Gen-Tie Facilities other than Permitted Liens and the Users shall not, directly or indirectly, create or incur any Lien on the Gen-Tie Facilities, and (II) the Interconnection Provider shall not, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any Lien on the Managed Assets arising out of the performance of its obligations under this Agreement (or default or breach in the performance of such obligations) other than those in clauses (a), (g) or (i) of the definition of Permitted Lien and the Users shall not, directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any Lien on the Managed Assets other than (in the case of the MA Users of such Managed Assets) those in clauses (a), (g) or (i) of the definition of Permitted Lien and those which the Interconnection Provider may create, incur or permit under this clause (II). As applicable, the Interconnection Provider and each User shall take prompt steps to discharge any Lien filed against any of the Gen-Tie Facilities or Managed Assets in violation of its obligations in the preceding sentence. If the Interconnection Provider or the User fails to discharge promptly any such Lien, the other Parties, in addition to any other rights it may have at law or equity for a breach of this Agreement, shall have the right to notify the responsible Party in writing and to take any reasonable action to satisfy, defend, settle or otherwise remove the Lien at the responsible Party’s expense (if the Interconnection Provider is the responsible Party such expense shall not be considered Interconnection Expenses hereunder). 5.4 Managed Assets. 5.4.1 Rights; Costs. The exercise of rights by a User with respect to the Managed Assets shall not impair the operation or reliability of the Gen-Tie Facilities. Each User shall be responsible for all costs of constructing and owning the Managed Assets, in accordance with its respective ownership interests in the Managed Asset as shown in Exhibit C and Interconnection Provider may, at the request of the Users, administer the collection of monies needed for the management, operation, maintenance, and repair of the Managed Assets. 5.4.2 Functional Control. By this Agreement, each User authorizes the Interconnection Provider to exercise functional control over the operation of Managed Assets as necessary to provide interconnection and transmission service across the Gen-Tie Facilities. Such control shall be exercised in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices, each respective User’s requirements and operating guidelines, and all applicable requirements of federal or state law or regulatory authorities; provided that the Users, and not the Interconnection Provider, shall be responsible for and shall ensure that the Managed Assets comply with all applicable reliability guidelines, policies, standards, rules, regulations, orders, or other requirements of NERC. Interconnection Provider shall permit each User that has an interest therein access to the Managed Assets to the extent of such User’s respective ownership interest therein, if any, as specified in Exhibit C hereto. 5.4.3 Interconnection Provider as Manager. Each MA User hereby engages the Interconnection Provider as an independent contractor of the MA Users to serve at the pleasure of the MA Users to manage, operate, and maintain the Managed Assets, and to perform other duties pertaining to the Managed Assets, all as set forth in this Agreement. Each MA User shall reimburse the Interconnection Provider for the costs and expenses of such management, operations and maintenance activities in an amount corresponding to its Undivided Interest in such Managed Assets. Such costs and expenses shall be invoiced to and paid by the applicable MA Users consistent with the procedures of invoicing and paying Interconnection Expenses as provided in Section 4.3. The Interconnection Provider accepts such engagement with respect to Managed Assets and agrees to perform such duties in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. Each of BF1 and BF2 individually hereby engages the Interconnection Provider as an independent contractor to serve at the pleasure of such Users to manage, operate, and maintain their respective Project Specific Assets, and to perform other duties pertaining to such Project Specific Assets, all as set forth in this Agreement. Each such User shall reimburse the Interconnection Provider for the costs and expenses of such management, operations and maintenance activities as to its Project Specific Assets. Such costs and expenses shall be invoiced to and paid by the applicable Users consistent with the procedures of invoicing and paying Interconnection Expenses as provided in Section 4.3. The Interconnection Provider accepts such engagement with respect to the Project Specific Assets owned by BF1 and BF2 and agrees to perform such duties in accordance with the terms and conditions hereof. As of or following the time that BF3 becomes a User, the Interconnection Provider may, but will not be required to, accept an engagement to provide management services for BF3’s Project Specific Assets. Each User shall grant to the Interconnection Provider any license or easements rights required for the Interconnection Provider to access the applicable Premises in connection with performing its obligations under this Section 5.4.3. 5.4.4 Managed Asset Decisions. All actions or decisions by the Interconnection Provider with respect to a Managed Asset that would impose costs on the MA Users of such asset not otherwise budgeted for shall require the Consent of the MA Users, which may then direct the Interconnection Provider accordingly, and only upon such direction (unless otherwise expressed herein), shall Interconnection Provider have authority to act on behalf of the relevant MA Users with respect to such matters.
